Funyula MP Paul Otuoma has picked former deputy county commissioner Solomon Abwaku as his running mate for Busia governor.He will face Governor Sospeter Ojaamong as an independent.Otuoma&rsquo;s supporters from Teso have praised the decision to settle on Abwaku, saying the move will help bring the people of Busia together. &ldquo;I have made up my mind to pick Abwaku as my running mate,&rdquo; Otuoma said on Friday.However, the move by the Funyula legislator has generated mixed reactions from Ojaamong&rsquo;s supporters.Some Ojaamong&rsquo;s supporters say Abwaku should have turned down Otuoma&rsquo;s offer and instead supported the incumbent. &ldquo;We now consider Otuoma&rsquo;s running mate a betrayer to Busia Governor Sospeter Ojaamong,&rdquo; a supporter, who sought anonymity, said.